  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "P. Patricius Byzantine official and historiographer,
    6th cent., Born in Thessaloniki about AD 500, died in 565 in Constantinople, East Roman official 
    and historiographer, first a lawyer in Constantinople, from 534 imperial envoy to the Goths of Italy.. 
    P. wrote historical works (only fragments of which have been preserved) about the Roman Empire (until 
    Constantius [2] II?), the office of magister officiorum up to the 6th cent., a lengthy passage of which 
    is preserved in the Book of Ceremonies (Constantine [9]) (1,84-95 Reiske), and about his peace mission in 561/2..." 
    from Tinnefeld, Franz (Munich). "Petrus." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and
    Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2011. Brill Online. Tufts University Library.</mads:note>
